  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Percentage of Participants with Suppression of Peak-Stimulated Luteinizing Hormone at 6 months.</measure>
    <time_frame>6 months</time_frame>
    <description>Luteinizing Hormone (LH) suppression is defined as peak-stimulated LH &lt; 4mIU/mL. Peak stimulated LH refers to the maximum LH concentration measured 30 minutes after a gonadotropin-releasing hormone agonst (GnRHa) stimulation test.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
